to the editor the varying blood pressure changes associated with visits to physicians offices when the white coats befuddle doctors aug 1 reflect the varying responses of patients to the medical environment when fear or anxiety prevails white coat hypertension occurs when comfort and confidence dominate white coat normotension results as a physician who occasionally exchanges his white coat for a patient 's gown i find myself so at home in the medical environment that my blood pressure is if anything lower than normal such variations call into question the existing data on the prevalence of hypertension as well as the parameters of its treatment dr stanley f wainapel new york

